Class RobotMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.illinois.mitra.starl.comms.RobotMessage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Traceable

    public class RobotMessage
extends java.lang.Object
implements Traceable
    The RobotMessage class is used to pass messages between agents. All messages have a recipient, sender, ID number, and contents. The ID number is used to target a message to a specific thread. Only threads which are registered MessageListeners for a particular ID will receive messages with that ID. No two threads may be registered for the same message ID.
    See Also:
    MessageListener, MessageContents
